 Let $(X, B)$ be a klt Calabi-Yau pair with $B 
eq 0$. Then there exists a birational contraction  egin{align*} \pi \colon X \dashrightarrow X' \end{align*} to a $\mathbb{Q}$-factorial Calabi-Yau pair $(X', B' =\pi_\ast B)$, $B'
eq 0$ and a tower of morphisms  egin{align} \label{mfs.tower.diag} \xymatrix{ X'=X_0 \ar[r]^{p_0} & X_1 \ar[r]^{p_1} & X_2 \ar[r]^{p_2} & \dots \ar[r]^{p_{k-1}}& X_{k} } \end{align} 
oindent such that  egin{enumerate} \item[(i)] for any $1 \leq i < k$ there exists a boundary $B_i 
eq 0$ on $X_i$ and $(X_i, B_i)$ is a klt Calabi-Yau pair, \item[(ii)] for any $0 \leq i < k$ the morphism $p_i\colon X_i 	o X_{i+1}$ is a Mori fibre space, with $ho(X_i/X_{i+1})=1$, and \item[(iii)] either $\dim X_k=0$, or $\dim X_k >0$ and $X_k$ is a klt variety with $K_{X_k} \sim_\mathbb{Q} 0$. \end{enumerate}
